            The introduction of foundational frontier models like <strong>GPT-5.6</strong> has fundamentally altered how enterprise applications are designed. Where previous generation models struggled with complex multi-step reasoning and required rigid prompt engineering, GPT-5.6 introduces native architectural reasoning, ultra-fast token streaming, and reliable structured JSON schema adherence.
          </p>
          <p>
            In modern custom software architecture, GPT-5.6 functions as an intelligent cognitive engine embedded directly within the application tier. Rather than building static, nested form layouts, software engineers now construct natural language interfaces where users can execute complex database operations through intuitive conversational commands.
          </p>
          <h3>High-Impact Enterprise Use Cases for GPT-5.6</h3>
          <ul class="styled-list">
            <li>
              <strong>Natural Language to SQL Analytics Copilots:</strong> Business analysts and department heads no longer need to write complex SQL joins or wait for IT reporting queues. By embedding GPT-5.6 with read-only database schemas, executives can type text queries such as <em>"Compare Q1 vs Q2 gross margins for our Kannur manufacturing plant grouped by SKU"</em> and receive instant interactive charts and validated data tables.
            </li>
            <li>
