          <h2>5. Autonomous AI Agents: The Software Revolution</h2>
          <p>
            Perhaps the most transformative engineering shift in 2026 is the transition from passive AI copilots to <strong>Autonomous AI Agents</strong>. Traditional software scripts are deterministic: they follow rigid <code>if-then-else</code> conditional trees and break the moment an unexpected input or edge case occurs. Early conversational chatbots were similarly limited, capable only of generating text without executing real-world actions.
          </p>
          <p>
            An Autonomous AI Agent is a complete cognitive loop. Armed with a system prompt defining its persona and boundaries, an AI agent utilizes an LLM as its reasoning engine to evaluate user intent, formulate a multi-step execution plan, call external APIs (tools) to read or write database records, observe the execution results, and dynamically correct its course until the objective is accomplished.
          </p>

          <!-- Diagram: Agent Architecture -->
          <div class="tech-diagram">
            <div class="diagram-title">Figure 2: Autonomous Enterprise AI Agent Execution Loop</div>
            <div class="diagram-boxes">
              <div class="d-box d-step1">User Request / Trigger</div>
              <div class="d-arrow">&rarr;</div>
              <div class="d-box d-step2">Cognitive Reasoning Engine (LLM)</div>
              <div class="d-arrow">&rarr;</div>
              <div class="d-box d-step3">API &amp; Tool Execution (SQL / CRM / Payment)</div>
              <div class="d-arrow">&rarr;</div>
