            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Why AI Agents Are Replacing Traditional Workflow Automation</h3>
          <p>
            Legacy enterprise automation tools relied heavily on brittle screen-scraping or rigid webhook integrations. If a third-party API field changed from <code>customer_id</code> to <code>clientId</code>, the entire automation pipeline failed silently. AI Agents possess semantic resilience; they understand schema definitions, interpret error messages dynamically, and can retry or re-route transactions gracefully without throwing fatal exceptions.
          </p>

